entry.tran: 无法居住的；不适合居住的
entry.def: If a place is uninhabitable, it is impossible for people to live there, for example because it is dangerous or unhealthy.

example.ex: About 90 percent of the city's single-family homes are uninhabitable...

example.ex: As parts of the world become uninhabitable, millions of people will try to migrate to more hospitable areas.
example.tran: 随着世界的一些地方变得不适人居，数以百万计的人将会试图迁移到环境更加宜人的地区。
